Samples from each treatment were examined every month for the following properties: weight loss and decay percentages; while dry weight, firmness, total soluble solids, and total soluble sugars were determined at 0, 2, 4 and 6 months of storage. The loss in weight percentage was calculated as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\text{Weight loss }}\left( \% \right) = \left( {{\text{W}}_{0} {-}{\text{ W}}_{{\text{n}}} } \right)/{\text{W}}_{0} \times { 1}00$$\end{document}

The decay percentage was calculated monthly as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\text{Decay percentage}} = \left( {{\text{W}}_{{\text{d}}} /{\text{W}}_{0} } \right) \, \times { 1}00$$\end{document}
